<p>

<b>The Rushmore Reviews</b> is a company based in <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../627/1627.xml">
Aberdeen</link></site>
, <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../994/26994.xml">
Scotland</link></country>
 that analyzes and provides data to the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../887/994887.xml">
oil industry</link>. It is a joint venture between two companies, Rushmore Associates and the Sigma Consultancy; both of whom remain independent to each other despite sharing the same offices and providing information through one web based portal.</p>
<p>

<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 The Rushmore Associates were founded by husband and wife Peter and Helen Rushmore. </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 The Sigma Consultancy by husband and wife Tim and Pat Stapenhurst.</entry>
</list>
</p>
<p>

The reviews began <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../598/34598.xml">
1993</link>, when a group of oil operators led by <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../720/18998720.xml">
BP</link></company>
 outsourced the production of the data collection and analysis project, they had been conducting since <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../670/34670.xml">
1988</link>, to the Rushmore Associates and the Sigma Consultancy.</p>
<p>

All the reviews data is accessed online and is available to companies that have signed up to the project through this internet portal.</p>
<p>

The reviews cover oil drilling projects around the world and send staff abroad to help other companies compile their own data for analysis and to aid them in implementing the companies data for their own use.</p>
<p>

The Rushmore Reviews are used by all the worlds major private and national oil companies.</p>

